------------------
Prerequisites
------------------
Java must be installed.

Ruby must be installed.

You need the following ruby gems:
gem install jsmin
gem install sprockets

You need JsTestDriver:
-environment variable JSTESTDRIVER_HOME must be set to e.g. c:\bin
-JsTestDriver-1.2.1.jar in e.g. c:\bin

-------------------
How to build srcjs
-------------------
1. goto tortage/lib
2. run: ruby makejs.rb
3. Then total js will by merged to: srcjs/deploy

--------------------------
How to run js tests
--------------------------
1. Start the jstestdriver server:
java -jar %JSTESTDRIVER_HOME%\JsTestDriver-1.2.1.jar --port 4224

2. Capture the browser by typing http://localhost:4224 in the browser. Select transactional or strict mode.

3. The test results will be shown in the browser. Requires that jsTestDriver.conf files are correctly setup.

